timeline.bodyText:
Instead of synchronizing the entire class(which leads to locking all methods of the class), it would be better to move this block into a private synchronized method. It would then look like,
public static void initialize() throws APIManagerDatabaseException {
        if (artifactSynchronizerDataSource != null) {
            return;
        }

        InitDataSource();
}

private static void InitDataSource() synchronized {
    .............
}

This would ensure that only callers of the initialize() method will have the potential of having to wait in a concurrent scenario, but callers of the getArtifactSynchronizerConnection() method will not be affected by this.

